Balanerpeton woodi is the oldest species, having been present over 330 million years ago during the Late Carboniferous.
The name Edopoidea is derived from the Greek words edo meaning "to bite" and pous meaning "foot". Edopoids are known as biting temnospondyls because their foot bones are so narrow that the edge of the foot fits tightly against the edge of the jaw.
